---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Terms of Service — EnDroit" description="EnDroit's Terms of Service. The rules and rights governing your use of our content management platform.">

  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container legal-container">

      <header class="legal-header">
        <div class="badge">Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: 13 May 2026 · Effective from: 1 June 2026</p>
      </header>

      <article class="legal-body">

        <p class="legal-intro">
          Welcome to EnDroit. These Terms of Service ("Terms") form a binding agreement
          between you ("you", "Customer", "Creator") and EnDroit ("we", "us", "EnDroit"),
          operated by Gillian Masse, headquartered in France. By creating an account,
          accessing the website at <a href="https://en-droit.app">en-droit.app</a>, or using
          any feature of our platform, you accept these Terms in full.
        </p>

        <h2>1. The service</h2>
        <p>
          EnDroit is a content management platform for legal education creators that helps
          them write, render and publish short-form vertical videos to social media platforms
          including TikTok, Instagram Reels and YouTube Shorts. The platform is delivered as
          a software-as-a-service via our website and provides multiple plans, including a
          free tier and paid subscriptions.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Eligibility and account registration</h2>
        <p>
          To use EnDroit, you must be at least 16 years old (or the digital-consent age in
          your country, whichever is higher) and able to enter into a binding contract under
          the laws of your jurisdiction. You must provide accurate registration details,
          keep your credentials confidential, and notify us immediately of any unauthorised
          use of your account.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may decline, suspend or terminate accounts at our reasonable discretion, in
          particular where we suspect fraud, misrepresentation, or breach of these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Subscriptions, billing and refunds</h2>
        <p>
          EnDroit offers monthly and annual subscriptions. Paid plans renew automatically
          unless cancelled by you before the next billing date. We bill in EUR via Stripe,
          our payment processor. All prices include applicable VAT for European Union
          customers.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may cancel a subscription at any time from your account settings. Cancellations
          take effect at the end of the current billing period and you retain access until
          that date. We provide pro-rated refunds only where required by applicable consumer
          law (notably, the EU 14-day withdrawal right for the initial subscription).
        </p>
        <p>
          We may change pricing with at least 30 days' notice. Price changes never apply
          retroactively to a billing period you have already paid for.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          You agree not to use EnDroit to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Publish content that is illegal, defamatory, fraudulent or that violates the rights of any third party;</li>
          <li>Misrepresent legal information in a way that could foreseeably harm a viewer (e.g. by presenting personal advice as a general statement of the law without disclaimers);</li>
          <li>Reverse-engineer the platform, attempt to access other users' accounts, or interfere with normal operation;</li>
          <li>Submit content you do not have the right to publish, including copyrighted footage, music or scripts;</li>
          <li>Use the platform for spam, automated mass posting, or any activity that violates the terms of the connected social-media platforms (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Content ownership</h2>
        <p>
          You retain full ownership of all content you upload, write, generate or publish
          through EnDroit ("Your Content"). By using the platform, you grant us a limited,
          worldwide, royalty-free licence to host, process, render and transmit Your Content
          for the sole purpose of providing you the service. This licence ends when you
          delete Your Content or close your account.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not claim any ownership over the videos you publish. You are responsible
          for ensuring that Your Content complies with applicable law and with the terms of
          the social-media platforms you publish to.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Connected accounts and third-party platforms</h2>
        <p>
          EnDroit enables you to connect external accounts (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube) so
          that we can publish content to them on your behalf, with your explicit consent.
          Each of these platforms has its own terms of service that you remain bound by.
          We are not responsible for changes to those terms, the availability of their APIs,
          or any decision they make regarding the content you publish through us.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          The platform integrates with the following third-party services, each governed by
          their own terms:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>TikTok Content Posting API</strong> — for publication to TikTok</li>
          <li><strong>Meta Graph API</strong> — for publication to Instagram Reels</li>
          <li><strong>YouTube Data API v3</strong> — for publication to YouTube Shorts</li>
          <li><strong>ElevenLabs</strong> — for optional voice synthesis</li>
          <li><strong>Pexels</strong> — for royalty-free background footage</li>
          <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — for payment processing</li>
          <li><strong>Anthropic</strong> — for AI-assisted script suggestions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Availability and changes to the service</h2>
        <p>
          We aim for high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted access. We may
          deploy updates, maintenance and feature changes at any time. Material changes that
          remove or reduce a feature will be announced with reasonable advance notice.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          EnDroit, including its name, logo, source code, interface, documentation and
          rendering engine, is the exclusive intellectual property of Gillian Masse and is
          protected by international copyright, trademark and other applicable laws. Nothing
          in these Terms grants you a licence to use these assets beyond your normal use of
          the service.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Warranty disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The service is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. To the maximum
          extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, whether express, implied or
          statutory, including warranties of merchantability and fitness for a particular
          purpose. Information generated or rendered by the service, including AI-assisted
          script suggestions, is provided for educational purposes only and does not
          constitute legal advice.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, our aggregate liability arising out of or
          relating to these Terms or the service shall not exceed the amount you paid us in
          the twelve months preceding the event giving rise to the claim. We are not liable
          for indirect, special, consequential or incidental damages.
        </p>
        <p>
          Nothing in these Terms excludes liability that cannot be excluded under applicable
          law, including in particular liability for gross negligence, wilful misconduct, or
          for personal injury caused by negligence.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          You may terminate your account at any time from your settings. We may terminate
          your access for material breach of these Terms with reasonable notice, or
          immediately for serious breach (fraud, illegal activity, security threat). Upon
          termination, your access ends, your data is retained for 30 days during which you
          may export it, and is then permanently deleted.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of France, without regard to its conflict-of-laws
          rules. For disputes with consumers, the consumer-protection rules of your country of
          residence apply where they grant you stronger protection. Any dispute that cannot
          be resolved amicably shall be submitted to the competent courts of Toulon, France,
          subject to mandatory consumer protections.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be announced by
          email and on the website at least 30 days before they take effect. Your continued
          use of the service after the effective date constitutes acceptance.
        </p>

        <h2>15. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Reach us at
          <a href="mailto:gillian83.masse@gmail.com">gillian83.masse@gmail.com</a>
          or via our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
        </p>

      </article>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding: 64px 0 32px; }
  .legal-container { max-width: 780px; }
  .legal-header { margin-bottom: 48px; padding-bottom: 28px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .legal-header .badge { margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .legal-header h1 { font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 44px); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .legal-meta { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); }

  .legal-intro {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 22px;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 36px 0 14px;
    padding-top: 6px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .legal-body h2:first-of-type { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; }
  .legal-body p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .legal-body ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .legal-body li {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .legal-body strong { color: var(--text); }
  .legal-body a { color: var(--accent); }
  .legal-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
